Dear Lisa:  As you requested, what follows is an example of  "exclusivity wording" that you might use in a contract.  Please note, however, that all contracts must be approved and initialled by Gerald Nemec or another attorney in EWS Legal before they are signed by an EWS officer. - Mary O.

Exclusivity.  In consideration of the efforts to be expended by Buyer in undertaking its due diligence review of the Project and Assets, Seller hereby grants to Buyer, during the Term of this Agreement (the "Exclusivity Period") the exclusive right to pursue the Project with Seller.  During the Exclusivity Period Seller shall not work with any other persons with regard to the Project or pursue any other transaction involving the Assets. 